'''Lee Kang-in''' ({{Korean|이강인}}; born 19 February 2001) is a South Korean professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as an [[attacking midfielder]] or [[winger (association football)|winger]] for {{French football updater|PSG}} club [[Paris Saint-Germain FC|Paris Saint-Germain]] and the [[South Korea national football team|South Korea national team]].

A product of [[Valencia CF|Valencia]]'s youth academy, Lee made his professional debut at the age of 17 in 2018, becoming the youngest South Korean footballer to debut professionally in Europe. In his debut season, he won the [[Copa del Rey]], before making his [[UEFA Champions League]] debut in his second professional season. Lee joined [[RCD Mallorca|Mallorca]] in 2021, before joining French side [[Paris Saint-Germain FC|Paris Saint-Germain]] in 2023. With PSG, he won three [[Ligue 1]] titles and two [[Coupe de France|Coupes de France]], including two [[UEFA Champions League]] titles back-to-back in [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League|2025]] and [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League|2026]], with the former being part of a [[continental treble]].

In 2019, Lee won the [[Asian Young Footballer of the Year]], the same year that he won the [[2019 FIFA U-20 World Cup]]'s [[FIFA U-20 World Cup#Golden Ball|Golden Ball]] award. Lee's team finished runner-up during the event. He later made his senior debut for South Korea in September 2019, representing his nation's squad for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] and [[2023 AFC Asian Cup]].

==Club career==

=== Valencia ===
Lee joined [[Valencia CF|Valencia]]'s academy in July 2011. On 15 December 2017, he was called up to [[Valencia CF Mestalla|Valencia B]] (Mestalla). He had his debut on 21 December 2017, in a match with [[Deportivo Aragón]], being substituted in the 82nd minute.{{Citation needed|date=October 2023}}

[[File:Lee Kangin 2019.png|thumb|200px|Lee with [[Valencia CF|Valencia]] in 2019]]
Lee made his first team debut on 30 October 2018, starting and playing 83 minutes in a 2–1 win over [[CD Ebro|Ebro]] in the [[2018-19 Copa del Rey#Round of 32|Copa del Rey]], becoming the youngest South Korean footballer to debut professionally in Europe.<ref>{{cite web|title=CD Ebro vs Valencia CF Live|url=https://www.laliga.es/en/other-competitions-live/temporada-2018-2019/copa-del-rey/4/ebro_valencia|publisher=La Liga|date=30 October 2018|access-date=27 November 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190331120033/https://www.laliga.es/en/other-competitions-live/temporada-2018-2019/copa-del-rey/4/ebro_valencia|archive-date=31 March 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref>

Lee made his [[La Liga]] debut on 12 January 2019, substituting in for [[Denis Cheryshev]] in the 86th minute in a 1–1 draw with [[Real Valladolid]] during [[2018-19 La Liga|2018–19 season]]. At 17 years, 10 months, and 24 days, Lee became the second youngest player in the 18–19 La Liga after [[Ander Barrenetxea (footballer)|Ander Barrenetxea]] from [[Real Sociedad]] who debuted at the age of 16 years, 11 months, and 24 days. He also became the youngest ever non-Spanish and the first Asian league debutant for Valencia, as well as the fifth Korean to play in La Liga.{{refn|group="note"|After [[Lee Chun-soo]] in 2003 for Real Sociedad, [[Lee Ho-jin (footballer)|Lee Ho-jin]] in 2006 for [[Racing de Santander|Racing Santander]], [[Park Chu-young]] in 2012 for [[RC Celta de Vigo|Celta Vigo]], and [[Kim Young-gyu (footballer)|Kim Young-gyu]] in 2013 for [[UD Almería|Almería]]}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.laliga.es/en/live/temporada-2018-2019/laliga-santander/19/valencia_valladolid|title=Valencia CF vs R. Valladolid CF Live|publisher=[[La Liga]]|language=es|date=12 January 2019|access-date=12 January 2019}}</ref>

On 30 January 2019, Lee officially joined the Valencia first-team, receiving jersey number 16.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.valenciacf.com/ver/98156/comunicado-oficial-i-kang-in-.html|title=Comunicado oficial I Kang In|publisher=Valencia CF|language=es|date=30 January 2019|access-date=30 January 2019|trans-title=Official announcement I Kang In}}</ref>

On 17 September 2019, Lee made his [[UEFA Champions League]] debut as a late substitute for [[Rodrigo (footballer, born 1991)|Rodrigo]] in a 1–0 win against [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]], becoming the youngest ever Korean to debut in the competition at the age of 18 years and 6 months, a record previously held by [[Jeong Woo-yeong]]. He also became the 5th youngest ever to debut for ''Los Ches'' in the same competition.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://english.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2019/09/19/2019091900944.html|title=Lee Kang-in of Valencia Makes Youngest Champions League Debut by Korean|date=19 September 2019|publisher=[[The Chosun Ilbo]]|language=en|access-date=19 September 2019}}</ref> On 25 September 2019, he scored his first La Liga goal in a 3–3 draw against [[Getafe CF|Getafe]], to become the youngest non-Spanish to score for Valencia, aged 18 years and 219 days old, breaking the previous record of [[Mohamed Sissoko]] who scored in the [[2003–04 UEFA Cup]]; and the third youngest ever, only behind [[Juan Mena]] and [[Fernando Gómez (footballer, born 1965)|Fernando Gómez]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/2019/09/26/Baseball/Lee-Kangin-scores-his-first-La-Liga-goal/3068376.html |title=Lee Kang-in scores his first La Liga goal |website=[[Korea JoongAng Daily]] |date=26 September 2019 }}</ref>{{refn|group="note"|On 1 November 2020, [[Yunus Musah]] broke Lee Kang-in's record, to become the youngest non-Spanish to score for Valencia, aged 17 years and 338 days.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.superdeporte.es/valencia/2020/11/01/musah-gol-record/477165.html |title=Musah, gol y récord |website=Super Deporte |language=es |date=1 November 2020 }}</ref>}} His record as the youngest non-Spanish goalscorer for Valencia was broken the following season by [[United States men's national soccer team|American]] teammate [[Yunus Musah]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://as.com/futbol/2020/09/13/primera/1600024191_615544.html|title=Yunus Musah, la última perla de la cantera che|trans-title=Yunus Musah, the last pearl of the ''che'' youth setup|publisher=[[Diario AS]]|language=es|date=13 September 2020|access-date=13 September 2020}}</ref>

On 13 September 2020, Lee became the youngest player, aged 19 years and 207 days, to assist two goals in a La Liga match in the 21st century, in a 4–2 win over [[Levante UD|Levante]], breaking the previous record of [[Juan Mata]] in 2008, aged 20 years and 150 days.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.goal.com/en/match/valencia-v-levante/cyq68c41heolcher3qrvdq238 |title=Valencia 4–2 Levante |publisher=Goal |date=13 September 2020 }}</ref> Despite rejecting several renewal offers from the club throughout the year,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://as.com/futbol/2020/11/14/primera/1605325816_417509.html|title=La venta de Kang-in Lee en enero, en la mesa de Peter Lim|trans-title=The sale of Kang-in Lee in January, on Peter Lim's desk|publisher=Diario AS|language=es|date=14 November 2020|accessdate=30 August 2021}}</ref> he featured regularly under [[Javi Gracia]]  as the ''Che'' ended [[2020–21 La Liga|the campaign]] on a mid-table position.

After being on the transfer list during the entire pre-season, Lee terminated his contract with Valencia on 29 August 2021.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.valenciacf.com/en/article/en-official-statement-kang-in-lee-2021-08-29|title=OFFICIAL STATEMENT {{!}} Kang In Lee|publisher=Valencia CF|date=29 August 2021|access-date=30 August 2021}}</ref>

===Mallorca===
On 30 August 2021, fellow La Liga club [[RCD Mallorca|Mallorca]] confirmed the free transfer of Lee, signing on a four-year contract.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.rcdmallorca.es/en/content/news/news/kang-in-lee-joins-rcd-mallorca-on-a-free-transfer|title=Kang In Lee Joins RCD Mallorca on a free transfer|publisher=RCD Mallorca|date=30 August 2021|access-date=30 August 2021}}</ref>

During the 2022–23 season, Lee became one of the best dribblers in the [[Big Five (association football)|Big Five]] European leagues by making the highest success rate of dribbles and the sixth highest number of successful dribbles.<ref>{{cite tweet |number=1660677953473200134 |title=Les 10 joueurs ayant réussis le plus de dribbles cette saison en championnat, le taux de réussite des dribbles et le ratio! |language=fr |author=Data´Foot |user=DTFootball_ |date=2023-05-23 |access-date=2023-07-09 |trans-title=The 10 players who completed the most dribbles this season in the league, the dribble success rate and the ratio!}}</ref><ref>{{cite tweet |number=1661024310528704513 |title=La crème de la crème |author=RCD Mallorca |user=RCD_Mallorca |date=2023-05-24 |access-date=2023-07-09 |trans-title=The best of the best}}</ref>

=== Paris Saint-Germain ===
[[File:FC Salzburg gegen Paris Saint-Germain UEFA Champions League 78 (Lee Kang-in).jpg|thumb|200px|Lee with [[Paris Saint-Germain FC|Paris Saint-Germain]] in 2024]]
On 8 July 2023, [[Ligue 1]] club [[Paris Saint-Germain FC|Paris Saint-Germain]] announced the signing of Lee on a five-year contract running through 2028, becoming the first ever South Korean to play for the club.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Lee Kang-In signs for Paris Saint-Germain |url=https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/lee-kang-in-signs-for-paris-saint-germain-until-2028 |access-date=2026-03-26 |publisher=Paris Saint-Germain FC |language=en}}</ref> A transfer fee of €22 million was paid out to Mallorca after Lee passed his medical at the start of June.<ref>{{Cite news |title=PSG reach agreement for Kang-In Lee |url=https://www.besoccer.com/new/psg-reach-agreement-for-kang-in-lee-1266549 |archive-url=http://web.archive.org/web/20231010105409/https://www.besoccer.com/new/psg-reach-agreement-for-kang-in-lee-1266549 |archive-date=2023-10-10 |access-date=2026-03-26 |language=en |publisher=BeSoccer}}</ref> 

On 12 August, he made his Ligue 1 debut in a 0–0 draw against [[FC Lorient|Lorient]] at the [[Parc des Princes]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Paris Saint-Germain V Lorient |url=https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/fixtures-and-results/202324/paris-saint-germain-v-lorient |access-date=2026-03-26 |publisher=Paris Saint-Germain FC |language=en}}</ref> On 25 October, he scored his first PSG goal and his first Champions League goal in a 3–0 victory over [[AC Milan]].<ref>{{Cite news |date=2023-10-25 |title=Paris Saint Germain 3-0 AC Milan: Kylian Mbappe on target in Champions League |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/67222948 |access-date=2026-03-26 |publisher=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> On 3 November, he scored his first Ligue 1 goal in a 3–0 win over [[Montpellier HSC|Montpellier]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Le PSG balaie Montpellier et devient provisoirement leader de la Ligue 1 |trans-title=PSG swept Montpellier and provisionally became Ligue 1 leader |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Paris-balaie-montpellier-et-devient-provisoirement-leader-de-la-ligue-1/1429651 |access-date=2026-03-26 |website=L'Équipe |language=fr}}</ref> On 3 January 2024, he was named man of the match, after he scored the opening goal in the 2–0 [[2023 Trophée des Champions|Trophée des Champions]] win over [[Toulouse FC|Toulouse]], where he won his first title with the club.<ref name=":0">{{Cite news |title=Trophée des Champions : Les meilleurs joueurs |trans-title=Champions' Trophy: The best players |url=https://ligue1.fr/Articles/Actu/2021/07/20/trophee-des-champions-les-meilleurs-joueurs |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240103223932/https://ligue1.fr/Articles/Actu/2021/07/20/trophee-des-champions-les-meilleurs-joueurs |archive-date=2024-01-03 |access-date=2026-03-26 |publisher=Ligue 1 |language=fr-FR}}</ref> As PSG won the [[Double (association football)|Double]] of the Ligue 1 and the [[Coupe de France]] in the [[2023–24 Paris Saint-Germain FC season|2023–24 season]],<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-05-26 |title=Lee Kang-in ends PSG debut with three titles after French Cup win |url=https://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/2024-05-26/sports/football/Lee-Kangin-ends-PSG-debut-with-three-titles-after-French-Cup-win/2054813 |access-date=2026-03-26 |website=Korea JoongAng Daily |language=en}}</ref> he became the first Asian player to win the Ligue 1.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-04-29 |title=Lee Kang-in wins first league title as PSG lock in Ligue 1 trophy |url=https://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/2024-04-29/sports/football/Lee-Kangin-wins-first-league-title-as-PSG-lock-in-Ligue-1-trophy/2035801 |access-date=2026-03-26 |website=Korea JoongAng Daily |language=en}}</ref>{{refn|group=note|He also became the second Asian player to win the Coupe de France. (The first winner is [[Ado Onaiwu]], who won the [[2022–23 Coupe de France|2022–23 edition]] with [[Toulouse FC|Toulouse]].)}}

In the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League|2024–25 season]], Lee became the second Asian ever to receive a UEFA Champions League medal, following compatriot [[Park Ji-sung]],<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-06-01 |title=PSG's Lee Kang-in becomes 2nd Korean to win UEFA Champions League title |url=https://www.koreatimes.co.kr/sports/20250601/psgs-lee-kang-in-becomes-2nd-south-korean-to-win-uefa-champions-league-title |access-date=2026-03-26 |website=The Korea Times |language=en}}</ref> but his playing time during the second half of the season decreased sharply due to [[Khvicha Kvaratskhelia]]'s arrival and [[Désiré Doué]]'s growth.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Napoli, ipotesi Kang-in Lee. Vuole cambiare aria, può fare tre ruoli |trans-title=Napoli, hypothesis about Kang-in Lee. He wants a change of scenery, he can play three roles |url=https://www.areanapoli.it/calciomercato/napoli-ipotesi-kang-in-lee-vuole-cambiare-aria-puo-fare-tre-ruoli_594099.html |access-date=2026-03-26 |website=AreaNapoli |language=it}}</ref> He considered his transfer in the summer despite winning a [[Treble (association football)|continental treble]],<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-06-02 |title=Calciomercato Napoli, Lee e Frattesi sono le priorità: gol e assist per Conte |trans-title=Napoli transfer market, Lee and Frattesi are the priorities: goals and assists for Conte |url=https://www.corrieredellosport.it/news/calcio/calcio-mercato/napoli/2025/06/02-141110386/calciomercato_napoli_lee_e_frattesi_sono_le_priorit_gol_e_assist_per_conte |access-date=2026-03-26 |website=Corriere dello Sport |language=it}}</ref> whereas the club was less willing to sell him actively.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://canal-supporters.com/mercato-lee-et-ramos-partis-pour-rester-au-psg-cette-saison/ |title=Mercato – Lee et Ramos, partis pour rester au PSG cette saison? |publisher=Canal Supporters |language=fr |date=2025-08-14 |access-date=2025-09-07|trans-title=Transfer window – Lee and Ramos, set to stay at PSG this season?}}</ref> On 15 June 2025, he came on as a 72nd-minute substitute and scored his first [[FIFA Club World Cup]] goal on a penalty kick in a 4–0 win over [[Atlético Madrid]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Le PSG corrige l'Atlético de Madrid pour son entrée dans la Coupe du monde des clubs |trans-title=PSG crushed Atlético Madrid in their Club World Cup debut |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Le-psg-corrige-l-atletico-de-madrid-pour-son-entree-dans-la-coupe-du-monde-des-clubs/1570468 |access-date=2026-03-26 |website=L'Équipe |language=fr}}</ref>

At the [[2025 UEFA Super Cup]] on 13 August, Lee was put into the field in the 67th minute when [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] held a 2–0 lead. He scored PSG's first goal, which underlay a 2–2 tie, and their third penalty goal in a 4–3 penalty shoot-out win.<ref>{{Cite web |last=<!-- Deny Citation Bot--> |title=Paris vs Tottenham {{!}} UEFA Super Cup 2025 Final |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefasupercup/match/2045107--paris-vs-tottenham/timeline/ |access-date=2026-03-26 |website=<!-- Deny Citation Bot--> |publisher=UEFA |language=en}}</ref> During the [[2025–26 Paris Saint-Germain FC season|2025–26 season]], he still remained a back-up for PSG as they secured their second successive Champions League title.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.worldfootball.net/teams/te1457/paris-saint-germain/statistics-matches/co19/champions-league/se104387/2025-2026/ |title=Paris Saint-Germain » Statistics: Appearances Champions League 2025/2026 |website=WorldFootball.net |access-date=2026-06-06}}</ref> While PSG's main players concentrated on winning the Champions League,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2026/may/29/arsenal-psg-champions-league-final-luis-enrique-ligue-1-mikel-arteta |title=Fresh v fatigued? Why PSG have a big advantage in Champions League final |website=The Guardian |publisher=Opta Analyst |date=2026-05-29 |access-date=2026-05-31}}</ref> he helped the club win their 12th Ligue 1 title in 14 years.<ref>{{Cite web |title=PSG's Dembele named UNFP Ligue 1 Player of the Year again |url=https://www.thescore.com/fra_fed/news/3539245 |access-date=2026-05-12 |website=theScore |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.worldfootball.net/teams/te1457/paris-saint-germain/statistics-matches/co71/france-ligue-1/se95139/2025-2026/ |title=Paris Saint-Germain » Statistics: Appearances Ligue 1 2025/2026 |website=WorldFootball.net |access-date=2026-06-06}}</ref> On 30 May 2026, he became the first Asian to lift multiple UEFA Champions League trophies when his teammates defeated [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] on penalties in the [[2026 UEFA Champions League final|final]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Howell |first=Alex |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cj6ppx48pk2t |title=Paris Saint-Germain 1–1 Arsenal (4–3 on pens) |publisher=BBC Sport |date=30 May 2026 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.koreatimes.co.kr/sports/20260531/psg-defend-champions-league-title-with-lee-kang-in-benched |title=PSG defend Champions League title with Lee Kang-in benched |website=The Korea Times |publisher=Yonhap News Agency |date=2026-05-31 |access-date=2026-05-31}}</ref>

== International career ==

=== 2019 U-20 World Cup ===
Lee was selected to play for the [[South Korea national under-20 football team|South Korea U-20 football team]] in the [[2019 FIFA U-20 World Cup]] and played in every group and knockout match, leading his team to a historic runner-up finish in the tournament and scoring two goals and four assists in seven games.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://sports.news.naver.com/kfootball/news/read.nhn?oid=529&aid=0000034579 |script-title=ko:[엠스플 축구] 지도자들 "이강인 '골든볼' 수상 대단하지만 걱정도 되는 게 사실" |language=ko |publisher=[[MBC Sports+]] |date=17 June 2019 |title=|trans-title=[M-S-PL Football] Coaches: "Lee Kang-in's 'Golden Ball' win is amazing, but it is true that we are also concerned"}}</ref> As a result, he received the Golden Ball award as the tournament's best player.<ref name="19 U-20 WC"/>

=== 2022 World Cup ===
Lee received his first call up to the senior [[South Korea national football team]] in March 2019 for friendlies against [[Bolivia national football team|Bolivia]] and [[Colombia national football team|Colombia]], and became the 7th youngest to be in the South Korean national team. On 5 September 2019, Lee made his international debut in a 2–2 draw friendly match against [[Georgia national football team|Georgia]] as a [[First XI|starter]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match?gameId=556647 |title=South Korea vs. Georgia – Football Match Summary – September 5, 2019 |date=5 September 2019 |publisher=ESPN |access-date=5 September 2019}}</ref>

Lee was called up for friendlies in September 2022 just before the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] by showing his evolution on both side of the ball in La Liga. He only participated in team training without appearances in the friendlies,<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.footballist.co.kr/news/articleView.html?idxno=155543 |script-title=ko:[9월 벤투호] '라리가 도움 1위' 이강인, 무력 시위 성공... 벤투까지 설득했다 |publisher=Footballist |language=ko |date=2022-09-13 |access-date=2023-01-15 |trans-title=[Bento's ship in September] 'La Liga Assist Leader' Lee Kang-in, succeeded in making a show of force... even persuaded Bento}}</ref> but was selected for the 26-men World Cup team.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://news.mt.co.kr/mtview.php?no=2022111213232561165 |script-title=ko:'안와골절' 손흥민, 월드컵 뛴다…이강인도 벤투호 승선 |publisher=Money Today |language=ko |date=2022-11-12 |access-date=2023-01-15 |trans-title='Orbital fracture' Son Heung-min will play at the World Cup... Lee Kang-in was also called up to Bento's ship}}</ref> He assisted [[Cho Gue-sung]]'s header with an accurate cross in the second group match against [[Ghana national football team|Ghana]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/12757305/world-cup-2022-south-korea-2-3-ghana-mohammed-kudus-scores-twice-in-pulsating-encounter |title=World Cup 2022 — South Korea 2–3 Ghana: Mohammed Kudus scores twice in pulsating encounter |publisher=Sky Sports |date=2022-11-29 |access-date=2023-01-15}}</ref>

=== 2023 Asian Cup ===
Lee was exempted from [[Conscription in South Korea|mandatory military service]] after winning the [[Football at the 2022 Asian Games – Men's tournament|2022 Asian Games]] in October 2023.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.france24.com/en/live-news/20231007-psg-s-lee-helps-south-korea-to-third-straight-asian-games-gold |title=PSG's Lee helps South Korea to third straight Asian Games gold |publisher=France 24 |date=7 October 2023 }}</ref> In a senior friendly against [[Tunisia national football team|Tunisia]] just after the Asian Games, he led South Korea to a 4–0 victory by scoring two goals including a free-kick goal, which were his first and second goals for senior national team respectively.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.foxsports.com/stories/soccer/jurgen-klinsmann-earns-first-home-win-as-coach-of-south-koreas-national-team |title=Jurgen Klinsmann earns first home win as coach of South Korea's national team |publisher=Fox Sports |date=13 October 2023}}</ref>

Lee was called up the South Korean squad for the [[2023 AFC Asian Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/2023-afc-asian-cup-jurgen-klinsmann-names-26-man-south-korea-squad-38788943 |title=2023 AFC Asian Cup: Jurgen Klinsmann names 26-man South Korea squad |publisher=OneFootball |date=28 December 2023}}</ref> He led South Korea to the knockout stage by scoring two goals in a 3–1 victory over [[Bahrain national football team|Bahrain]] and having a free-kick goal and an assist from a corner in a 3–3 draw with [[Malaysia national football team|Malaysia]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/lee-guides-south-korea-3-1-asian-cup-over-bahrain-2024-01-15/ |title=Lee guides South Korea to 3–1 Asian Cup win over physical Bahrain |publisher=Reuters |date=15 January 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.interfootball.co.kr/news/articleView.html?idxno=623226 |script-title=ko:[IN-STAR] '득점 2위-베스트11 2회'...이강인 시대 알렸다! 토너먼트에서도 부탁해 |publisher=InterFootball |language=ko |date=2024-01-27 |access-date=2024-01-27|title=|trans-title=[IN-STAR] '2nd top scorer - two Best 11 awards'... Lee Kang-in's era has begun! Please keep it up at the knockout tournament as well}}</ref> He created the highest number of key passes and successful crosses until the quarter-finals.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.the-afc.com/en/national/afc_asian_cup/news/q-finals_in_numbers_2.html |title=Quarter-finals In Numbers |publisher=AFC |date=2024-02-05 |access-date=2024-02-08}}</ref> After South Korea was eliminated in the semi-finals by [[Jordan national football team|Jordan]],<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.goal.com/lists/son-heung-min-south-korea-asian-cup-semi-finals-jordan-tottenham/blt1339884221ff08b4#cscf5c23e93771f58d |title=Son Heung-min sent packing! South Korea dumped out of the Asian Cup semi-finals by underdogs Jordan as talisman prepares to return to Tottenham |publisher=Goal |date=2024-02-07 |access-date=2024-02-07}}</ref> however, it was reported that he had been in conflict with veteran players in the national team including captain [[Son Heung-min]] before the defeat.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://biz.chosun.com/sports/baseball/2024/02/14/NK4LQ5C7UC2QUWDT6FBLUWIULE/ |script-title=ko:손흥민과 몸싸움→주장 포함 고참급 선수단, "이강인 명단에서 빼달라" 감독에게 요청 |language=ko |publisher=[[The Chosun Ilbo]] |date=2024-02-14 |access-date=2024-02-18|title=|trans-title=Physical altercation with Son Heung-min... veteran players including the captain asked manager to "remove Lee Kang-in on the list"}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-02-20 |title=Lee Kang-in vs. Son Heung-min — what actually happened? |url=https://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/2024-02-20/sports/football/Lee-Kangin-vs-Son-Heungmin--what-actually-happened/1984670 |access-date=2026-05-31 |website=Korea JoongAng Daily |language=en}}</ref>

==Media==
In 2007, the six-year-old Lee was featured in the third season of the [[Korean Broadcasting System|KBS]] N Sports reality football show [[Fly Shoot Dori]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Meet Lee Kang-in – Valencia's South Korean starlet with an €80 million release clause |url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/news/meet-lee-kang-in-valencias-south-korean-starlet-with-an-80/5x9pzgvn6jm51jdzagdyac3hs |publisher=Goal |access-date=27 November 2018 |date=24 November 2018}}</ref> After his exceptional performance, he passed through [[Yoo Sang-chul]]'s youth academy and in 2009 joined the [[Incheon United FC|Incheon United]] U-12 youth team. He later attended Seokjeong Elementary School in [[Incheon]] and played for Flyings FC.<ref>{{cite web |title=MEET LEE KANG-IN – THE NEXT GREAT SOUTH KOREAN TALENT BY SHAY HICKS |url=https://footballtalentscout.net/2022/10/28/meet-lee-kang-in-the-next-great-south-korean-talent-by-shay-hicks/ |publisher=Football Talent Scout |access-date=19 February 2024 |date=28 October 2022}}</ref> In January 2011, he went to [[Spain]] under the recommendation of his youth team coach and took part in trials for the youth teams of Spanish clubs [[Villarreal CF|Villarreal]] and [[Valencia CF|Valencia]].<ref>{{cite web |title=MPSG colleagues who showed off their friendship with 'Lee Kang-in and two-shot certification' |url=https://medium.com/@dydgkdl8/psg-colleagues-who-showed-off-their-friendship-with-lee-kang-in-and-two-shot-certification-10a360df84ba |website=Medium |access-date=19 February 2024 |date=13 July 2023}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Lee was born on 19 February 2001 in [[Incheon]], the youngest of three children. His father Lee Woon-seong was a taekwondo instructor in Incheon and a big football fan (especially of [[Diego Maradona]]).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news1.kr/articles/?3645906 |script-title=ko:"깡돌아 결승전서 골 기대할게"…이강인 외할머니 응원 |website=News1 |language=ko |date=15 June 2019 |trans-title="Kkang-dol, I'll be expecting a goal in the final"... Lee Kang-in's maternal grandmother cheers him on}}</ref>

